article.headline: Campbell 78, North Florida 48
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Jonathan Rodriguez scored 24 points and grabbed 14 rebounds, leading Campbell to a 78-48 win over North Florida Tuesday. North Florida (2-11, 0-3 Atlantic Sun conference ) controlled the first 13 minutes of the game, leading by as many as six points before the Camels battled back. A pair of free throws by North Florida's Germaine Sparkes pushed the Ospreys ahead 23-17 with 7:33 to play. But a 14-2 run by the Camels erased that advantage. Campbell led 32-29 at the half. Campbell pushed out to a 10-point lead in the first three minutes of the second half, and a 16-0 run after that put the game out of reach. Campbell also outrebounded North Florida 47-28. Russ Gibson added 19 points and 10 rebounds for the Camels (6-5, 1-0), making it his third double-double of the year. Chris Timberlake led the Ospreys with 14 points, and Aaron Caruthers added 13.
